{"questionId":"22322424","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mstyle mathvariant=\"italic\"><mo stretchy=\"true\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">)</mo></mstyle><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>evidence of increase in winning prize&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;</em>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong>(number of price increases =) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mfenced><mi>X</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</strong>for game&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mfenced><mi>X</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;for game&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn></math>, etc.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:40px;\"><strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></strong></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:40px;\"><strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;</strong>(games)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>(calculation of winnings to make the game fair)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>w</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mo>$</mo></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>evidence of increase in winnings per game up to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>$</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>$</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>$</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;</strong>(games)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22322424","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.12bi","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}